Github workflow:

To add a new feature:
1. add a new branch
    git checkout master
    git checkout -b <branch_name>
    git push origin <branch_name>
2. add new features
    git commit -a -m 'changes'
    git push
3. merge master to the branch
    git merge master --no-ff
    resolve conflicts
4. create a pull-request to master through github web-interface
